<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1876,1972]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
The nominotypical subgenus was characterized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stary" box="[731,902,1876,1900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" refString="Stary, J. (1998) New species of Trichocera Meigen, 1803, with a re-assessment of the subgenera Trichocera s. str. and Metatrichocera Dahl, 1966 (Diptera, Trichoceridae). Studia Dipterologica, 5 (2), 175 - 186." type="journal article" year="1998">
J. Starý (
<number box="[832,893,1876,1900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The main features are found in aedeagal complex, which has short and basally arched parameres that slightly exceed length of aedeagus and more or less fused with each other to produce membranous roof of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
